    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Cash Drag",
      "explanation_en": "Cash drag refers to the performance penalty a portfolio suffers when it holds uninvested cash during a rising market. Today's risk-on rally illustrates the cost: our $269 in idle cash earned nothing while stocks climbed. Maintaining a minimum cash threshold is good for flexibility, but holding too much cash too long can erode returns relative to a benchmark like VOO.",
